<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Vanish" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Vanish,</orth> (conjugated with <emph>to be</emph>) to disappear: <bibl n="shak. son 63.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 63, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.216" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 216</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.598" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 598</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.275" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 275</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.52" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.288" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 288</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.5" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 5, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.220" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 220</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 12, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.300" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 300</bibl> (== to die; cf. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 67</bibl>). <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.350" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 350</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.473" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 473</bibl>. <emph>--ed</emph> == gone, past: <cit><quote>he runs and chides his --ed loathed delight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 742" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 742</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>moan the expence of many a --ed sight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 30.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 30, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>picked from the worm-holes of long --ed days,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 86</bibl></cit>.<lb />Used of breath issuing from the mouth: <cit><quote>which, thronging through her lips, so vanisheth as smoke from Aetna,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1041" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1041</bibl></cit>. Hence, perhaps, the singular expression: <cit><quote>a gentler judgment --ed from his lips,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 10</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="1309" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>